you.example: Definition: To address (a person) using the pronoun you (in the past, especially to use you rather than thou, when you was considered more formal).

do.example:
Definition: A party, celebration, social function.
Example: “We’re having a bit of a do on Saturday to celebrate my birthday..”

know.example: Definition: Knowledge; the state of knowing.

who.example: Definition: A person under discussion; a question of which person.

i.example:
Definition: The name of the Latin-script letter I.
Example: “the position of an i-dot (the dot of an i).”

my.example:
Definition: Used to express surprise, shock or amazement.
Example: “My, what big teeth you have!.”

name.example:
Definition: Any nounal word or phrase which indicates a particular person, place, class, or thing.
Example: “I've never liked the name my parents gave me so I changed it at the age of twenty..”

this.example: Definition: Something being indicated that is here; one of these.

me.example:
Definition: As the direct object of a verb.
Example: “Can you hear me?.”

a.example: Definition: The name of the Latin script letter A/a.

time.example:
Definition: The inevitable progression into the future with the passing of present and past events.
Example: “Time stops for nobody.   the ebb and flow of time.”

big.example: Definition: Someone or something that is large in stature

and.example: Definition: In rhythm, the second half of a divided beat.

learn.example: Definition: The act of learning something

cooler.example: Definition: Having a slightly low temperature; mildly or pleasantly cold.

hi.example:
Definition: The word "hi" used as a greeting.
Example: “I didn't even get a hi..”

new.example:
Definition: Things that are new.
Example: “Out with the old, in with the new..”

word.example: Definition: The smallest unit of language that has a particular meaning and can be expressed by itself; the smallest discrete, meaningful unit of language. (contrast morpheme.)

will.example:
Definition: (now uncommon or literary) To wish, desire (something).
Example: “Do what you will..”

are.example: Definition: An accepted (but deprecated and rarely used) SI unit of area equal to 100 square metres, or a former unit of approximately the same extent. Symbol: a.

listening.example:
Definition: To pay attention to a sound or speech.
Example: “Please listen carefully as I explain.  I like to listen to music..”

speaking.example:
Definition: Used in speaking.
Example: “one's normal speaking voice.”

can.example:
Definition: (auxiliary verb, defective) To know how to; to be able to.
Example: “She can speak English, French, and German.   I can play football.   Can you remember your fifth birthday?.”

tell.example: Definition: A reflexive, often habitual behavior, especially one occurring in a context that often features attempts at deception by persons under psychological stress (such as a poker game or police interrogation), that reveals information that the person exhibiting the behavior is attempting to withhold.

what.example: Definition: (Singlish) Used to contradict an underlying assumption held by the interlocutor.

stop.example:
Definition: A (usually marked) place where buses, trams or trains halt to let passengers get on and off, usually smaller than a station.
Example: “They agreed to meet at the bus stop..”

hearing.example:
Definition: (stative) To perceive sounds through the ear.
Example: “I was deaf, and now I can hear..”

speak.example: Definition: A low class bar, a speakeasy.

microphone.example: Definition: A device (transducer) used to convert sound waves into a varying electric current; normally fed into an amplifier and either recorded or broadcast.

ka.example: Definition: A spiritual part of the soul in Egyptian mythology, which survived after death.

definition.example: Definition: A statement of the meaning of a word or word group or a sign or symbol (dictionary definitions).

baby.example: Definition: A very young human, particularly from birth to a couple of years old or until walking is fully mastered.

never.example:
Definition: At no time; on no occasion; in no circumstance.
Example: “I finally finished, and I never want to do that again..”

things.example: Definition: That which is considered to exist as a separate entity, object, quality or concept.

that.example: Definition: Something being indicated that is there; one of those.

example.example: Definition: Something that is representative of all such things in a group.

beginners.example:
Definition: Someone who is just starting at something, or has only recently started.
Example: “I'm new to learning Japanese: I'm just a beginner..”

meaning.example: Definition: (of words or symbols) The entity, perception, feeling or concept thereby represented or evoked.

ing.example:
Definition: A meadow, especially a low meadow near a river; water meadow.
Example: “Ings, glens, and fens of the Highlands..”

pens.example:
Definition: An enclosure (enclosed area) used to contain domesticated animals, especially sheep or cattle.
Example: “There are two steers in the third pen..”

the.example:
Definition: With a comparative or with more and a verb phrase, establishes a correlation with one or more other such comparatives.
Example: “It looks weaker and weaker, the more I think about it..”

highlands.example: Definition: An area of high land.

in.example:
Definition: A position of power or influence, or a way to get it.
Example: “His parents got him an in with the company..”

vocabulary.example: Definition: A usually alphabetized and explained collection of words e.g. of a particular field, or prepared for a specific purpose, often for learning.

start.example:
Definition: The beginning of an activity.
Example: “The movie was entertaining from start to finish..”

reading.example:
Definition: To look at and interpret letters or other information that is written.
Example: “Have you read this book?.”

begging.example: Definition: The act of one who begs.

bola.definition: A throwing weapon made of weights on the ends of a cord.

taking.example:
Definition: To get into one's hands, possession or control, with or without force.
Example: “I'll take that plate off the table..”

we.example: Definition: (personal) The speakers/writers, or the speaker/writer and at least one other person (not the person being addressed). (This is the exclusive we.)

like.example:
Definition: (usually in the plural) Something that a person likes (prefers).
Example: “Tell me your likes and dislikes..”

it.example: Definition: One who is neither a he nor a she; a creature; a dehumanized being.

en-hi-language.example:
Meaning (noun):
Description: A body of words, and set of methods of combining them (called a grammar), understood by a community and used as a form of communication.
Example: “Deaf and mute people communicate using languages like ASL..”
Description: The ability to communicate using words.
Example: “the gift of language.”
Description: A sublanguage: the slang of a particular community or jargon of a particular specialist field.
Example: “legal language;   the language of chemistry.”
Description: The expression of thought (the communication of meaning) in a specified way; that which communicates something, as language does.
Example: “body language;   the language of the eyes.”
Description: A body of sounds, signs and/or signals by which animals communicate, and by which plants are sometimes also thought to communicate.
Description: A computer language; a machine language.
Description: Manner of expression.
Description: The particular words used in a speech or a passage of text.
Example: “The language he used to talk to me was obscene..”
Description: Profanity.

Meaning (verb):
Description: To communicate by language; to express in language.

en-hi-then.example:
Meaning (conjunction):
Description: Used in comparisons, to introduce the basis of comparison.
Example: “she's taller than I am;  she found his advice more witty than helpful;  we have less work today than we had yesterday;  We had no choice than to return home.”
Description: (obsolete outside dialectal, usually used with for) Because; for.

Meaning (noun):
Description: That time
Example: “It will be finished before then..”

Meaning (adjective):
Description: Being so at that time.

Meaning (adverb):
Description: (temporal location) At that time.
Example: “He was happy then..”
Description: (temporal location) Soon afterward.
Example: “He fixed it, then left..”
Description: (sequence) Next in order; in addition.
Example: “There are three green ones, then a blue one..”
Description: In that case.
Example: “If it’s locked, then we’ll need the key..”
Description: (sequence) At the same time; on the other hand.
Example: “That’s a nice shirt, but then, so is the other one..”
Description: (affirmation) Used to contradict an assertion.
